  <h2>What Is a High-Yield Savings Account?</h2>
  <p>A high-yield savings account works exactly like a regular savings account — you deposit money, earn interest, and withdraw when needed. The difference is the interest rate. While traditional banks offer a paltry 0.01% to 0.10% APY, the best high yield savings accounts compared here offer 4.00% to 5.25% APY.</p>
  <p>Most high-yield accounts are offered by online banks, which have lower overhead costs than brick-and-mortar institutions. They pass those savings on to you in the form of higher interest rates. Your deposits are FDIC-insured up to $250,000, so there's no additional risk.</p>

