  <h2>How to Choose the Best High Yield Savings Account</h2>
  <p>When comparing the best high yield savings accounts, APY is important but not everything. Consider these factors:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>APY stability</strong> — Some banks offer promotional rates that drop after a few months. Look for banks with a track record of consistently competitive rates.</li>
    <li><strong>Fees</strong> — The best accounts charge zero monthly fees. Avoid any account that eats into your interest earnings.</li>
    <li><strong>Access to funds</strong> — How quickly can you transfer money out? Some banks offer same-day transfers; others take two to three business days.</li>
    <li><strong>Minimum balance requirements</strong> — Most top accounts have no minimums, but some require a balance to earn the advertised APY.</li>
    <li><strong>FDIC insurance</strong> — Confirm the bank is FDIC-insured. All accounts listed above are fully insured.</li>
    <li><strong>Additional features</strong> — Buckets, sub-accounts, linked checking, and mobile app quality can make a real difference in daily use.</li>
  </ul>

